Hi! Thank you for your question! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, the syntax is as follows:

if (condition) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to execute if the condition is false
}

Where "condition" is a Boolean expression that determines whether the if block or else block will be executed.
